{"questionId":"9070284","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Calcium carbonate reacts with hydrochloric acid.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">CaCO<sub>3</sub>(s) + 2HCl(aq) → CaCl<sub>2</sub>(aq) + H<sub>2</sub>O(l) + CO<sub>2</sub>(g)</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Describe how the activation energy of this reaction could be determined.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong><em>ALTERNATIVE 1:</em></strong></p>\n<p>carry out reaction at several temperatures</p>\n<p>plot <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{{\\text{T}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>T</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;against log rate constant</p>\n<p><em>E</em><sub>a</sub> = – gradient <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\times \">\n  <mo>×</mo>\n</math></span>&nbsp;R</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><em>ALTERNATIVE 2:</em></strong></p>\n<p>carry out reaction at two temperatures</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>determine two rate constants</p>\n<p><strong><em>OR</em></strong></p>\n<p>determine the temperature coefficient of the rate</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>use the formula&nbsp; <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\ln \\frac{{{k_1}}}{{{k_2}}} = \\frac{{{E_{\\text{a}}}}}{R}\\left( {\\frac{1}{{{T_2}}} - \\frac{1}{{{T_1}}}} \\right)\">\n  <mi>ln</mi>\n  <mo>⁡</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>k</mi>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>k</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>E</mi>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>a</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>R</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>T</mi>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>T</mi>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Accept “gradient </em>= <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{ - {E_{\\text{a}}}}}{R}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>E</mi>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>a</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>R</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><em>” for M3.</em></p>\n<p><em>Award both M2 and M3 for the formula&nbsp;&nbsp;</em><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{ln}}\\frac{{rat{e_1}}}{{rat{e_2}}} = \\frac{{{E_{\\text{a}}}}}{R}\\left( {\\frac{1}{{{T_2}}} - \\frac{1}{{{T_1}}}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>ln</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>E</mi>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>a</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>R</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>T</mi>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>T</mi>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p><em>Accept any variation of the formula,&nbsp;</em><em>such as </em><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{rat{e_1}}}{{rat{e_2}}} = {e^{ - \\frac{{{E_{\\text{a}}}}}{R}\\left( {\\frac{1}{{{T_1}}} - \\frac{1}{{{T_2}}}} \\right)}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>e</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mfrac>\n          <mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <msub>\n                <mi>E</mi>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mtext>a</mtext>\n                </mrow>\n              </msub>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n        </mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>(</mo>\n          <mrow>\n            <mfrac>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mrow>\n                <mrow>\n                  <msub>\n                    <mi>T</mi>\n                    <mn>1</mn>\n                  </msub>\n                </mrow>\n              </mrow>\n            </mfrac>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mfrac>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mrow>\n                <mrow>\n                  <msub>\n                    <mi>T</mi>\n                    <mn>2</mn>\n                  </msub>\n                </mrow>\n              </mrow>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>)</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p><strong><em>[3 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9070284","referenceCode":"18M.2.hl.TZ1.4d","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Describe how the activation energy of this reaction could be determined.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 16: Chemical kinetics","16.2 Activation energy","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 16: Chemical kinetics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}